# Prisma schema changes — use migrations

**Canonical rule:** `prisma-migrations.mdc`

For normal work:

1. `npx prisma migrate dev --name <name>`
2. `npx prisma migrate deploy` on production (Railway) before/after deploy when migrations ship

`prisma db push` and `npm run db:push:all` are **not** the default path when `prisma/migrations/` exists — they bypass migration history and cause "table does not exist" in other environments.

Only use `db push` for disposable local experiments, never for changes you will commit.
